article.headline: Bowling Green 81, Ohio Dominican 55
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio -- Danny McElroy and Joe Jakubowski led a balanced Bowling Green attack with 12 points each, and the Falcons cruised to an 81-55 victory over Ohio Dominican Monday night. Scott Thomas, Jordon Crawford and A'uston Calhoun had 11 each for the Falcons (1-1). Ohio Dominican (0-2) committed 23 turnovers to Bowling Green's eight. Nevertheless, the Panthers led 23-19 when Morgan Jones made a 3-pointer with 7:45 left in the first half. But that was as good as things got for the Panthers, who were outscored 22-8 the rest of the half and trailed 41-31 at the break. The Falcons went on a 10-0 run early in the second half to stretch the lead to 15 points (51-36). Zak Kapron's layup interrupted the run, which Bowling Green immediately resumed by scoring another 19 in a row to put the game out of reach. John Trew had 13 points off the bench to lead the Panthers and Kapron added 11.
